1) On the thermometer question, it wasn't clear wether "Republicans" and "Democrats" included voters, or just politicians (which makes a big difference). 2) For the first scenario (a Republican governor vetoes a bill passed by a Democratic congress and widely supported by the public), it was difficult to evaluate how un-/democratic and un-/fair it was, as the description was missing some crucial information. The basic principle of a democracy is "majority rule, minority rights". While the governor's action violated the first part, this is acceptable if it's in service of the second.
